The paper discusses a central tool in data analysis and learning, specifically kernel principal component analysis (KPCA), which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper proposes a new approach for streaming KPCA, which suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of random feature maps, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and matrix sketching, which is a technique in information theory (cs.IT).
